  "texts": [
    "Ahmed et al. [62] reported that mixes with up to 10% RHA did not show any significant changes in fresh properties, indicating that low RHA content does not noticeably affect these properties.",
    "Numerous studies have demonstrated that adding GGBFS can impact the setting times and workability of concrete.",
    "For instance, Yun et al. [65] observed that incorporating GGBFS at replacement levels of 20%, 40%, and 50% led to a reduction in setting times by 5-10%, while higher GGBFS content extended setting times by 15-20%.",
    "Similarly, Moghadam et al. [66] and Zou et al.",
    "[67] both noted that increasing GGBFS content, up to 45% and 30% respectively, resulted in a decrease in workability and slump by 5-20%."
  ],
